  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a dim, wood-lined interior with a large bright window on the left. A young adult woman with dark hair, wearing a pale cream riding outfit, sits near the window with one leg raised. She is pulling on a tall, glossy black riding boot, using both hands to work it over her foot and calf. Her posture is upright and composed, and she looks down toward the boot with a slight smile as she adjusts it into place.\n\nA close view then shifts to a wooden surface near the same window. Resting on the surface is a small wristwatch or watchband: a narrow black band with shiny silver-toned metal at one end, lying in a gentle curve. A black riding boot moves in the background, reinforcing the equestrian setting. A hand reaches in from above, pinches the silver end of the band, and lifts it from the wood.\n\nThe woman appears again standing by the bright window, now wearing a dark riding jacket over her light shirt and cream trousers. Tack or straps hang on the wall behind her, suggesting a stable or riding room. She adjusts her clothing, then lifts a black riding helmet or hat over her head and settles it into place.\n\nA close-up focuses on her wrist and cuff. The white cuff of her shirt peeks out from beneath the dark jacket sleeve, and a checked shirt or vest pattern is visible in the background. Around her wrist is the featured black watchband, narrow and sleek, with silver-toned metal along the sides and at the attachment point. Her other hand runs along the band, touching and turning it to show its surface and construction. She gently pulls and flexes the band, demonstrating that it stretches and moves around the wrist rather than fastening like a conventional leather strap. The black surface has a smooth, leather-like look, while the silver edges catch the light as her fingers rotate it.\n\nThe final images move to a dark, dramatic riding scene. The woman is now mounted on a dark horse, dressed in her black riding helmet, dark jacket, light shirt, cream riding pants, and polished black boots. Bright star-shaped flares from lights shine across the dark background, creating a glossy, theatrical atmosphere. The horse’s head and ears are visible beside her as she sits upright in the saddle, holding the reins. The black riding outfit, the dark horse, the gleaming boot, and the sparkling highlights echo the sleek black-and-silver appearance of the watchband identified in the audio context as the Lady Romunda by Speidel.",
